Abstract = {{1. The immigration and rise to dominance of Picea abies within Fiby
   Forest, Sweden, was investigated by pollen and charcoal analysis of tiny
   (c.1-m2) bogs which contained a 4000-year record.
   2. A mixed deciduous forest that existed 4000 years ago was replaced in
   a stepwise manner by a boreal community. The detailed dynamics of the
   changeover were controlled by catastrophic disturbances 2500 and 2200
   years ago.
